Reason: multiple inter-service trace durations (p95/mean) rise across checkout/cart/shipping/payment, indicating increased RPC latency, but that can be caused by network latency or by service-side CPU/processing delay. To disambiguate, check:
- whether_is_abnormal_metric for container CPU load (checkoutservice-*, cartservice-*) around the anomaly times, and for node CPU spike;
- whether_is_abnormal_metric for container network packet retransmission/packet loss and interface RTT on the nodes hosting those containers;
- collect_trace on the affected call chain to see span-level breakdown (client send, network transit, server processing).
